<RcpE name="Polenta With Dried Porcini - {Polenta Con Porcini Secchi}" author="Mary Ann Esposito">
<RTxt>
<![CDATA[                      
* Exported from MasterCook *

        Polenta With Dried Porcini - {Polenta Con Porcini Secchi}

Recipe By     :Mary Ann Esposito
Serving Size  : 10    Preparation Time :0:00
Categories    : Italian                         Rice/Grains

  Amount  Measure       Ingredient -- Preparation Method
--------  ------------  --------------------------------
  2               cups  dried porcini mushrooms - (abt 2 oz)
  6        tablespoons  olive oil
  2                     garlic cloves -- minced
                        Salt -- to taste
                        Freshly-ground black pepper -- to taste
  1             recipe  Polenta -- (see recipe),
                        chilled

In a small bowl, soak the porcini in water to cover for 1 hour.

Drain the porcini, reserving the soaking liquid, and cut into dice.  Strain the soaking liquid and set aside.

In a skillet, heat the olive oil.  Add the garlic and saute until soft.  Add the porcini and 1/4 cup of the reserved soaking liquid, cover, and simmer for 5 minutes.  Add salt and pepper.

Meanwhile, cut the cold polenta into 10 thick slices.  Place them on a lightly greased broiler pan or grill rack and broil or grill them until lightly browned.  Carefully transfer the slices to a serving platter, top with the porcini mixture, and serve.

This recipe yields 10 servings.

Comments:  A good polenta dish is enhanced by a balance of flavors.  By itself, polenta is rather bland, but when you match it with an ingredient with a definite flavor, like woodsy-tasting porcini, then you have a real culinary marriage.

