                     Tuscan Herb Rub - {Erbe Toscane}

Recipe By     :Mary Ann Esposito
Serving Size  : 0     Preparation Time :0:00
Categories    : Condiments                      Italian
                Rubs

  Amount  Measure       Ingredient -- Preparation Method
--------  ------------  --------------------------------
  2               cups  rosemary needles
  1                cup  sage leaves
  4              large  garlic cloves
  2          teaspoons  coarse salt
                        = (Diamond Kosher is best)

Make a pile of the rosemary, sage, garlic and salt on a cutting board.  Use a chef's knife or a mezzaluna (rocking knife) and mince the ingredients.  Spread the mixture on the cutting board or on paper towels and allow it to dry overnight.

Transfer the mixture to a jar and store it in the refrigerator.

Use it to rub on pork roasts, chicken, mix it into sauteing vegetables and soups.  It makes a great little culinary gift, too.

Vary the herbs and add herbs like thyme, lemon zest, fennel seeds, or fennel pollen.

This recipe yields 3 cups.

Comments:  One of the things I have learned in the Tuscan kitchens that I have visited is that one must always have a jar of erbe toscane (Tuscan herbs) on hand for rubbing into roasts and using for general cooking.  The most favored herbs are rosemary, sage, and garlic.  This is a great way to utilize the herbs in your garden.

